===Etymology===
[[File:Carnival venice 2015 137.JPG|thumb|People in masquerade ''(sense 2)'' at the {{w|Carnival of Venice}} in [[Venice]], [[Italy]], in 2015]]

The {{glossary|noun}} is borrowed from {{bor|en|frm|mascarade}}, {{m|frm|masquarade}}, {{m|frm|masquerade}} (modern {{cog|fr|mascarade|t=masquerade, masque; farce}}), and its {{glossary|etymon}} {{der|en|it|mascherata|t=masquerade}}, from {{m|it|maschera|t=mask}} + {{m|it|-ata}}. {{m|it||Maschera}} is derived from {{der|en|ML.|masca|t=mask}}: see further there. The English word is cognate with {{cog|LL.|masquarata}}, {{cog|pt|mascarada}}, {{cog|es|mascarada}}.<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=n.'' and ''adj|id=114657|date=December 2000|nodot=yes}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=n}}</ref>

The {{glossary|verb}} is derived from the noun.<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=v|id=114658|date=December 2000|nodot=yes}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=v}}</ref>

